data.meta_description:
2,614 likes, 55 comments - honkytonktown on April 2, 2024: "Happy Birthday to Emmylou Harris! #77
.
April 2nd: On this day 1947
Born on this day in Birmingham, Alabama, was Emmylou Harris, singer-songwriter and musician. She has released many chart-topping albums and singles over the course of her career, winning 12 Grammy Awards. Her first Country #1 was in 1976 with her version of the Buck Owens song “Together Again.”
.
The album “Elite Hotel” released in 1975 had Rodney Crowell on electric guitar and backing vocals and also Linda Ronstadt - backing vocals.
Harris’ vocals on the album earned her the Grammy Award for Best Country Vocal Performance, Female.
.
Harris has been estimated to have sold over 15 million records worldwide.
She has also earned 13 Grammy Awards, placed 27 singles into the top ten of the US country chart, and several of her albums have received gold certifications in the US.
She was inducted into the Country Music Hall of Fame in 2008 and was ranked among Rolling Stone’s list of the 200 Greatest Singers of All Time in 2022.
.
On 20 June 1977, she recorded a TV Special for AVRO’s TopPop with her Hot Band consisting of:
Glen D. Hardin, piano
John Ware, drums
Albert Lee, lead guitar
Hank DeVito, pedal steel guitar
Rodney Crowell, guitar
Emory Gordy Jr, bass.
.
